<br>
I disagree. While melee classes are heavily dependent on eqipment, casters are only dependent on resist gear. Most casters already exceed the AC softcap and the additional points, while they look nice on your Magelo profile, mean diddly squat as far as performance.<br>
<br>
Mana gear? Well, yes to a degree, but even the best mana gear only affords 2 extra casts of most high end spells. Besides, if you have C3 up, mana regen negates alot of the need for mana quantity.<br>
<br>
Focus items? Well, if you are raiding you have a mage there. Perma items are nice, but summoned will work just fine.<br>
<br>
HP? HP gear will help somewhat to negate AE damage, but no caster is going to stand up to direct melee for more than 2 or 3 rounds. Use LoS and resists as they are much more effective than HP.<br>
<br>
So, while I agree with you on melee, casters simply require the spells, good resists and some raid smarts imo.<br>
