<br>
Add the length of the average fight against a top Luclin mob (20-30mins, or more) and you get into a situation where the only thing that matters, as a caster, is how fast you are regenning mana, because this equates directly to how soon you can cast your next heal or nuke, and have a net zero, or at least very small, mana loss over that time.<br>
<br>
I will agree with you that caster gear that boosts hp, AC, resists and mana is not super crucial. However, gear that boosts mana regen is so crucial its not funny. Practically every decent caster loot that drops off a top Luclin uber mob has a healthy chunk of FT on it - eg. FT 5 robes and tunics, FT 6 shields, FT 3 and 4 Range slot items, FT 6 rings, and so on. In 2-3 kills (of mobs like Burrower and Cursed esepcially - hell, Cursed even drops a ranger *only* weapon that has FT 4 on it =), you can easily see a total of over 15 FT &quot;points&quot; drop.<br>
<br>
Mana regen is where its at in Luclin - you need very decent amounts of it to last through the marathon battles against Luclin's uber mobs. Caster gear, specifically FT gear, is very, very important against Luclin uber mobs (and I'm talking about the top rank here - mobs like AL, HP, Cursed, Emperor, Seru, VT I imagine). Luclin gear can now make a big difference between casters, just as Velious gear made a huge gap between those melee who had ToV N/Vulak/ST loot and those who didn't.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
