<DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=00FF00, strength=2)"><center><a style="font-family:Verdana; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none; font-size:10pt"href=http://pub8.ezboard.com/fthecompanionswebboardfrm30>The Companions Recruitment Official</a></center></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umandoman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandoman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 321<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/18/02 12:34:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EV = Fuckwads</span><hr size=1> Forgot the other variance besides just the DPS/TDPS. Actual damage done<br>
<br>
Non Geared Wizard<br>
<br>
21 cycles at 1200 damage for a total of 25,200 damage before needing rods in the example.<br>
<br>
<br>
Geared Wizard<br>
<br>
32 cycles at 1984 damage for a total of 63,488 damage before needing rods in the example.<br>
<br>
So, the geared wizard will output 60 percent more damage, while taking twice as long before needing the use of MR2s in the example.<br>
<br>
At the very least you need to concede that gear will make as drastic difference for wizards equalling the difference in gear between a uber/nonuber monks/rogues/other dmg dealing melee (only ones to really compare them to since they are melee equivalents). Stay away from blanket statements bro. <p><br><br><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22676" target=blank><IMG SRC="http://4.65.47.107/mandosig4.jpg" border="0"></a></center>
<DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=00FF00, strength=2)"><center><a style="font-family:Verdana; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none; font-size:10pt"href=http://pub8.ezboard.com/fthecompanionswebboardfrm30>The Companions Recruitment Official</a></center></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ugrozzer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grozzer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/18/02 5:27:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EV = Fuckwads</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Xaviera wrote:<br>
... back before Kunark even. How many warriors had over 1200 AC and over 4K hp back then. Oneton and Pigg ... how many others ?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't remember anyone having those statistics pre-Kunark. Back then it was a miracle to have 1000 AC. Also, Oneton and Pigg were in TA in those days, while EV warriors had better equipment. I think the most senior TA warriors had AC in the 900s. The best-equipped warrior on the server would have been Crush.<br>
<br>
Ogre warriors had more hitpoints in those days because other warriors did not max their stamina. AC was considered more important as nobody had discovered a soft cap and the concept of MTs with CH chains had not yet developed.<br>
<br>
--<br>
